    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-30T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-30T20:00:00-05:00" n="1059"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1059">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.93114A/6–2644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-30T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 30, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2226. Financial Assistance, Occupied China. An increase of 50 percent in the
                    financial assistance payments authorized by Department’s 2160, June 24 is hereby
                    authorized effective June 1st (Legation’s 4074, June 26<note n="73"
                        xml:id="d1059fn73">Not printed.</note>).</p>
                <p>You may authorize Fontanel to use the 9,000,000 CRB dollars released by the
                    Japanese (Legation’s 3905, June 19<note n="74" xml:id="d1059fn74">Not printed;
                        but for summary, see footnote 70, <ref target="#pg_1038">p.
                        1038</ref>.</note>) in making payments for June.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
